    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but \"feeling\" something doesn't make the pain any less real, it just makes it more exhausting. if the end result is always going to be nothingness, then why do we have to go through the whole exhausting process of suffering just to get there? it feels like we're just prolonging the inevitable. if we knew for a fact that an end was coming, wouldn't it be more logical to just reach it on our own terms rather than waiting for the universe to slowly drain the life out of us?",
